{{Otheruses|Blue Level}}
'''Blue Level''' was the middle deck of the three passenger levels on the ''[[Errant Venture/Legends|Errant Venture]]'', [[Booster Terrik]]'s personal [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]]. It played host to mildly-respectable passengers and acted as a base of operations for multiple traders, [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]], [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]], mercenaries and [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]]. It was the location of the majority of the ship's docking areas. Blue Level was also home to [[Trader's Alley]], a cash-only bazaar, and three-deck central courtyard that linked it to [[Diamond Level]]. The courtyard contained high holodiorama depicting the [[Battle of Thyferra]], with Booster's role enhanced and his son-in-law Corran's role nearly eliminated. Despite the questionable historical accuracy, it was considered one of the greatest pieces of wartime art in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] following the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

